<Base title="About — Pixel Noise" description="Learn about Pixel Noise — a blog covering design, UI/UX, graphic design, tools, and the design community.">

  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>About</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="content-page-body" style="padding: 0;">
      <p>Pixel Noise is a design-focused publication covering UI/UX, graphic design, design tools, hardware and software, industry news, and the stories and rumors shaping the creative community. It exists as a space to think out loud, share what's worth reading, and document what's happening in design right now.</p>
      <p>Every article on Pixel Noise is written with one goal in mind: to be genuinely useful or genuinely interesting to designers who care about their craft. Whether it's an analysis of a product's visual direction, a roundup of tools worth your time, or an honest take on where the industry is heading — this is that kind of writing.</p>
      <p>Pixel Noise is written by one author with the assistance of AI — not to replace editorial judgment, but to support it. Every piece is reviewed, edited, and published by a real person who cares about what gets put out into the world.</p>
      <p>The goal is simple: build an audience of designers and creatives who trust Pixel Noise to surface what matters, week after week.</p>

      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>For submissions, feedback, advertising inquiries, or collaboration — reach out at <a href="mailto:hello@pixelnoise.dev" style="color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: underline;">hello@pixelnoise.dev</a>.</p>
      <p>You can also follow and connect via social links listed in the footer.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
